    source: "WEG40100 The Planets Collection p.237",
    summary: "Korbin is a lawless criminal haven — a played-out mining colony turned galactic dumping ground for convicts. The Old Republic resettled dangerous prisoners here, honest workers fled, and the inmates now run the prison. There is no government, no law, and no restrictions on weapons, substances, or behavior. The only rule is 'the one with the biggest blaster makes the rules.' All four cities are cruelly named Pleasant, Happy, Joy, and Peace. The black market sells everything at 2-3x markup, with a 1-in-6 chance items are defective. Disease is rampant (Easy STR roll per day in Pleasant City or contract illness). The 'Last Call' is a 700m-deep valley used as a mass grave. Korbin's one legitimate product is kyrf — a potent alcoholic fruit liquor from Drelmar Bin's 900 sq km plantation.",
    locations: "Pleasant City (largest, starport, no customs, tumbledown prefabs + stone buildings, disease-ridden). Happy, Joy, Peace ('Small-Timers', smaller cities). Last Call (700m deep valley, mass grave, scrub lizards + necresh rodents). Kyrf Plantation (900 sq km, 10km NE of Pleasant City, Drelmar Bin's estate, power fence, mercenary guards, processing plant). Selenfer Pass (Pleasant↔Happy) and Refin Pass (Joy↔Peace) — both bandit-infested. Equatorial mountain range girdles the planet. Redeye (blood-red moon, barren, tidal effects). Grillis asteroid belt (Cross-Galactic Mining). Abatrang (gas giant, ammonia atmosphere).",
    ofNote: "LAWLESS PLANET — no government, no weapon restrictions, no customs inspections. Black market prices 2-3x normal. 2D roll on purchase: '2' = item breaks at worst time, '12' = never works. Easy STR/day in Pleasant City or contract disease. Kyrf liquor: Very Easy STR for first glass, +1 difficulty per glass, fail by 10+ = instant unconsciousness, lasts 12 hours. Scrub lizards: 3m desert predators (STR 4D, blood frenzy +1D STR/DEX on wound, +1D armor). Draz: vicious canine packs (STR+2D teeth). Necresh: carrion rodents in Last Call valley. Salvage crews work the system — 'finders keepers' law. Kara Saffch: ethical salvager, Night Havok (modified YT-1300, fire control 4D twin laser). Drelmar Bin: corrupt plantation owner, killed previous owner to take over. | SERON'S CASTLE (WEG40062 Wanted by Cracken p.47): Gornt Seron's organization operates from a huge, ancient castle in the Korbin Equatorial Range mountains, standing on a mountain ledge towering above a canyon. Only reachable by flying — small docking facility on eastern side holds up to 10 ships/vehicles, requires pre-arranged clearance from Seron or Jontin. Unscheduled vehicles are approached by armed airspeeders and shot down if answers are unsatisfactory. Ground guard station below the castle has four repulsorlift vehicles. Sensors implanted in a 2km radius detect unannounced guests. The hangar bay is built into the ledge supporting the castle, guarded by five guards at all times (Difficult sneak to enter unnoticed). A balcony rings the entire castle, guarded by two pairs of patrolling guards (Moderate climbing to reach; Very Difficult sneak to avoid detection). Stealth entry: Very Difficult climbing without ropes (Moderate with gear) from the guard station to hangar or balcony; failed roll means falling, but Very Difficult lifting/STR allows grabbing a handhold. | SERON'S PERSONNEL: Guards — former slaves, mercenaries, and ex-Imperial soldiers; rag-tag appearance. DEX 3D (blaster 4D, blaster artillery 4D+2, brawling parry 4D, melee combat 4D, melee parry 4D), KNO 2D (languages 3D+2), MEC 2D (repulsorlift operation 4D), PER 3D (bargain 4D+1, con 4D+2, gambling 5D, hide 4D+1, search 5D, sneak 4D), STR 3D (brawling 4D+1, stamina 4D), TEC 2D (security 3D+2). Equipment: blaster pistol (4D), some carry heavy blaster pistols (5D) or blaster rifles (5D); comlink, glowrod. | Enforcers — a cut above the guards, ensure the organization is not threatened by outside forces; also serve as Seron's messengers at gambling houses. DEX 4D (blaster 6D, blaster artillery 5D+2, brawling parry 5D, dodge 5D, grenade 5D, melee combat 5D, melee parry 4D+2), KNO 3D (alien species 5D, bureaucracy 4D+2, intimidation 5D+1, streetwise 4D), MEC 2D+2 (beast riding 4D, repulsorlift operation 5D, starship gunnery 4D+2, starship shields 4D+2), PER 2D (bargain 3D, con 4D, gambling 4D, hide 3D+2, search 5D, sneak 4D), STR 3D+1 (brawling 5D+1, lifting 4D, stamina 4D), TEC 3D (security 4D). Equipment: heavy blaster pistol (5D), comlink, protective vest (+1 to chest)."
