    techLevel: "Space",
    majorExports: "Starships",
    majorImports: "Raw materials, metals, starship components",
    source: "WEG40217 Platt's Starport Guide p.54",
    summary: "Kuat is the home of the legendary Kuat Drive Yards, whose immense orbital construction docks nearly blot out the stars above the planet. The system's primary employers are KDY and the Imperial Navy, which maintains a massive presence overseeing and protecting both KDY's commercial yards and dedicated naval shipyards. Kuat itself is a privileged world reserved for the system's elite — a planet of rolling forests dotted by small cities and grand estates, broken only by the occasional immense city, Imperial government complexes, KDY administrative offices, and Kuat Control Central, the system's main traffic hub managing millions of ships, passengers, and tons of supplies daily. Security is intense and layered, with blaster weapons prohibited on the surface.",
    locations: "Kuat Drive Yards (massive orbital stardock ring surrounding the system's sun, Star Destroyers and capital ships under construction, serviced by fleets of construction tugs and space barges). Kuat Passenger Port (orbital station, primary civilian entry point, heavy customs and security screening, stringent documentation requirements for surface access). Kuat Control Central (system traffic control station managing millions of ships daily). Surface estates and cities (privileged residential areas for system elite, rolling forests, small cities, monorail network connecting suburbs to starport areas). Imperial government complexes (multiple surface installations). KDY administrative offices (surface headquarters).",
    ofNote: "Blaster weapons are prohibited on Kuat's surface — carrying one violates local codes and draws ISB attention. Multiple layers of security between the Passenger Port and the planet surface; forged documentation may be needed to gain surface access. ISB maintains active operations ships and agents throughout the system. Kuat Passenger Port has underworld contacts who can forge travel permits. Monorail network connects starport suburbs. Escape from Kuat requires navigating through the massive KDY stardock ring — threading past Star Destroyers under construction, through fleets of construction tugs, with likely TIE fighter patrols in pursuit. The orbital construction yards are so extensive they are visible from the surface, nearly blocking out the sky. ~35 billion people work in the orbital facilities around Kuat, housed in floating residential/commercial stations closer to Kuat than the stardocks. Access to Kuat surface requires a series of permits and ID verifications — passes needed even for visiting relatives or social engagements. Rolling wooded hills are popular recreation for the rich; sections near the main planetary starport reserved for common shipyard workers."
