    majorExports: "None (transfer station)",
    majorImports: "None (transfer station)",
    source: "WEG40217 Platt's Starport Guide p.38",
    summary: "Kuat Passenger Port is a massive orbital transfer station in the Inner Kuat Transfer Zone, far from Kuat itself but closer than the outer traffic staging systems. All civilian passengers bound for Kuat or the Core Worlds pass through here. The station consists of four docking hemispheres — Outbound Dome (non-Core flights), Core Dome (Core Worlds flights), Military Dome (Imperial military transfers), and Kuat Dome (dedicated Kuat system flights) — surrounding a central sphere housing Kuat Central Plaza. Electronic signs reset every 20 hours regularly show passenger tallies reaching upwards of two billion. No commercial or passenger starships are allowed into the Kuat system itself; all traffic is handled by dedicated Imperial Navy shuttles and container ships running between the ports and Kuat proper.",
    locations: "Kuat Central Plaza (central sphere, small city in itself, houses passenger control, starport security, quarters for 500,000+ staff, dining, lodging, shops, medical and security stations). Outbound Dome (flights to/from ports outside Core Worlds, docking arms for liners, docking bays for yachts/shuttles/freighters). Core Dome (Core Worlds originating/destination flights, all craft require Core transit permits and security clearance). Military Dome (Imperial military traffic, transfers between military and civilian flights, departure/arrival for Imperial Transfer Post). Kuat Dome (dedicated flights to/from inner Kuat system and KDY stardock facilities). Customs Security Checkpoints (immense mazes of queues between each dome, ID/travel/clearance verification, security sensor scans of luggage). High-Speed Tubeway Transit System (beneath dome floors, ovoid repulsorcraft guided by droid brains, seats 4 with luggage, acceleration/deceleration compensators, average trip under 2 minutes).",
    ofNote: "Direct hyperspace travel to Kuat system is forbidden and physically impossible — the stardock ring extends so far out that hyperdrives cut out before reaching the system. Approach requires plotted routes through traffic corridors with clearance from Kuat Control at each stage. Three-ring traffic structure: outer ring (traffic staging systems), inner ring (transfer zone with three high ports), core (Kuat system). Passenger Port staging systems: Ulion (3hr wait, 21min jump) and Redrish (2hr wait, 16min jump). Freight Port staging: Monadin (8hr wait, 12min jump) and Horthav (6hr wait, 23min jump). Imperial Transfer Post staging: classified. Docking fees: 150 cr/day (light freighters) to 2,000 cr/day (large liners). Core Worlds Travel Clearance requires: Ship's Operating License (BoSS), Captain's Accredited License, Arms Load-Out Permit (for armed ships), Ship's Transponder Verification, Cargo Bay Tax (10 cr/metric ton cargo space or 25 cr/passenger accommodation), and Core Worlds Travel Clearance document. Violations in BoSS databanks = denied clearance and impound/imprisonment. Weapons forbidden in Passenger Port — customs scanners detect energy weapons, visual searches for melee weapons, explosives guarantee imprisonment. Narcotics (especially spice) forbidden, though Kuat elite have access via Imperial channels. Export of starship technology strictly forbidden — violators 'disappear.' Live organism imports subject to quarantine. Aliens not permitted living quarters in Kuat system — must reside in staff apartments at the port. Notable NPCs (see Notable NPC Lookup on NPC tab): Sergeant Reggis Thine (security officer, helpful to free-traders), Benni (pack tracker/information broker), Captain Dorai (Duros transport pilot, trades KDY info for galactic news), Benja Da'aapp and Olaal Da'aapp (Gruvian tourists with legitimate Core Worlds clearance)."
