    gravity: "Standard",
    terrain: "Swamp hilltop settlement",
    lengthOfDay: "30 standard hours",
    lengthOfYear: "287 local days",
    sapientSpecies: "Humans, Quarren, Sullustans, Twi'leks, various other aliens",
    starport: "Standard class",
    population: "10,000",
    function: "Starport, trade hub, criminal haven",
    government: "Anarchy (unofficial Sullustan administration by Loro Eels)",
    techLevel: "Space",
    majorExports: "Shvash gas, vohis mold",
    majorImports: "Foodstuffs, high technology, starship parts",
    source: "WEG40217 Platt's Starport Guide p.56",
    summary: "Gelgelar Free Port is the only city and starship facility on the swamp planet of Gelgelar, run by an enterprising Sullustan named Loro Eels and his extensive family. Built on a dry hill in the middle of the swamps, the town is a collection of ramshackle buildings encircled by landing pads where the city meets the marsh. The starport's navigational beacon is normally kept off — approaching pilots call in on an open comm channel, and starport controllers (all Sullustans speaking their native language) verify the vessel is not Imperial or pirate before activating the beacon. Once a ship lands, the beacon is deactivated and a controller collects the docking fee. Traffic is extremely light: at most one ship per hour during busy times, sometimes none for days. No flight plans, no departure clearance, and no customs authority of any kind.",
    locations: "Port Control and Beacon (eastern edge of town, beacon normally off as anti-Imperial precaution). Nofre Repair Bay (immense hangar at main starport, holds 1 bulk freighter or up to 4 light freighters; run by Nofre Eels with all-Sullustan mechanic staff on duty day and night; five ancient Z-95 Headhunters parked inside for port defense). Gelgelar Outfitters (two-story general store, first floor retail with maze of bins and shelves, upper floor Eels family quarters, dry storage basements below; run by Qulo Eels). Fenn's Landing (7 independent platforms in northeast section run by Slerog Fenn, a greedy Rodian — 20 cr/day docking, poor repair service at double cost, 10-day waits for parts; security goons who also steal from docked ships). Slippery Gelgelar Eel (cantina next to Shrine of Kooroo, run by Thulls the Ithorian — information broker, blaster rifle under the bar, raises prices when pilgrims or brash spacers arrive). Red Threxa's Boarding House (15 cr/night, converted prefab units with huge heating unit, run by a shifty Suiraon lizard-being who sleeps behind his registration desk). Shvash Gas Cooperative (run by Vleen Argoe, buys gas at 50 cr/ton, sells 75–120 cr/ton plus 25 cr tank deposit; traders can resell to mini-flamer companies for 150 cr/ton). Farmers' Landing and Warehouses (southeast section, warehouses hold up to 2,500 tons of vohis mold; managed by Brack who buys at 100 cr/ton, sells at 150–200 cr/ton; food companies typically pay 220–250 cr/ton despite Brack's claims of 400 cr/ton).",
    ofNote: "No customs, no tariffs, no Imperial presence. Illegal goods pass through freely. All starport controllers speak Sullustan as an anti-Imperial security measure — spacers who don't speak Sullustan will struggle. Docking fees: 10 cr/day at main starport platforms (Eels-owned), 20–50 cr/day at independent platforms on the swamp's edge (quality varies — some platforms sink under a ship's weight). Only repair services are at Nofre Repair Bay; independent platform mechanics charge double and parts take up to 10 days. Loro Eels ensures fair trade and protects spacers from being cheated while also ensuring local businesses get their share of off-world credits. He is rumored to live in a warren of watertight passages beneath the starport and part of the town. Eels is wanted by SoroSuub Corporation for smuggling, spacejacking, and other crimes. He provides forged starship and pilot documents for a price. Notable NPCs (see Notable NPC Lookup on NPC tab): Loro Eels (unofficial mayor/entrepreneur), Nofre Eels (master mechanic/repair bay operator), Qulo Eels (general store owner/cargo buyer), Slerog Fenn (rival docking platform operator), Thulls (bartender/info broker at Slippery Gelgelar Eel), Brack (warehouse manager), Vleen Argoe (shvash gas dealer), Varrik (mechanic at Fenn's Landing), Red Threxa (boarding house owner), plus Fenn's Security Goons, Sullustan Mechanics, and Gelgelar Outfitters Clerks."
