    lengthOfDay: "26 standard hours",
    lengthOfYear: "312 local days",
    sapientSpecies: "Human/Naboo (N), Gungans (N)",
    starport: "Stellar",
    population: "1.2 billion humans, unknown number of Gungans",
    function: "Cultural center, homeworld",
    government: "Democracy/monarchy (humans), tribal (Gungans)",
    techLevel: "Space",
    majorExports: "Art",
    majorImports: "High technology",
    source: "REUP Star Wars RPG: Revised Expanded Updated p.472",
    summary: "Naboo is a Mid Rim world of peculiar geology — it lacks a molten core, instead possessing a honeycombed interior surging with luminous plasma. Wide shallow seas separate flat plains of nola grass and the occasional elevated region such as the Gallo Mountains. The amphibious Gungans evolved here, building a tribal militaristic society to defend against semi-sentient bursa quadrupeds. Mysterious first colonists occupied Naboo more than five millennia ago, then vanished leaving only stone statues. Human colonists from the world of Grizmallt arrived later; after initial hostilities, the Naboo and Gungans settled into an uneasy truce — the Gungans retreating to underwater bubble cities, the Naboo colonizing the continental heartlands. The planet is governed by an elected monarch and was represented in the Senate by a Chommell sector delegate. In 32 BBY, Darth Sidious arranged a Trade Federation invasion as a pretext for accumulating political power, vaulting his alter ego Palpatine from Senator to Supreme Chancellor. The Jedi quelled the immediate crisis. Palpatine's homeworld connection was an open secret during the Empire; Naboo housed his private retreat, and his former security chief Panaka became Moff of the Chommell sector. The planet's population resisted the Empire throughout, and celebrated Palpatine's death.",
    locations: "Theed (capital city of the Naboo; seat of the elected monarch; site of the Royal Palace; established end of the Time of Suffering circa 800 BBY). Otoh Gunga (primary Gungan underwater bubble city; established 3000 BBY after the unification of Gungan boss clans; ruled by Boss Nass). The Gallo Mountains (elevated terrain in the continental interior).",
    ofNote: "Homeworld of Emperor Palpatine (Darth Sidious) — a fact that made Naboo a politically complicated world throughout the Imperial era. The underwater plasma veins and cave systems connecting the planet's interior are a navigational hazard but also a potential escape route. Sando aqua monsters and other giant sea creatures inhabit the deep waters. The Gungan military uses unique plasma-ball weaponry and personal energy shields. Theed is one of the most architecturally beautiful cities in the galaxy — domed rooftops, waterfalls, and green plazas."
