    aliases: ["Yavin Prime"],
    source: "WEG40119 Galaxy Guide 2: Yavin and Bespin p.9–10",
    summary: "Yavin is a massive gas giant with an equatorial diameter of 192,478 km and an atmosphere 65,000 km deep. Its mass (323.7 Standard) and gravity (2.74G) make it a powerful moon-trap — it hosts at least 22 moons, including the habitable Yavin 4. Banded in greens, yellows, blacks, grays, and tans by winds exceeding 600 kph at the equator, its cyclonic storm-spots range from 12,000 to 35,000 km in diameter. The planet glows and shimmers from internal light refraction through its deep atmosphere. Beneath the frozen ammonia upper clouds lie layers of ammonium-hydrosulfide and frozen water crystals, above a core of metallic hydrogen under pressures exceeding 1.28 million kg/cm². At the core-atmosphere boundary, 134 species of flattened 'crawlers' have been observed. The upper atmosphere hosts dozens of floater species — vast gasbag creatures drifting on the wind — including two predatory types. Corusca gems form deep in Yavin's atmosphere and are occasionally harvested by daring miners, though the pressure and predators make extraction extremely dangerous.",
    locations: "Upper atmosphere (floater habitat; ammonia crystal layer). Mid-atmosphere (ammonium-hydrosulfide layer; floater shark and floater squid territory). Lower atmosphere / core boundary (crawler habitat; humanoid-lethal pressure zone).",
    ofNote: "Atmospheric creatures (all Starfighter scale): Non-Predatory Floater (STR 4D+, Move 70/200 kph, 30–1,500m long — threat via mass collision), Floater Shark (STR 6D, Move 175/500 kph, 30–50m — attacks anything including ships; only turbolasers or ramming effective), Floater Squid (STR 6D, 10–50 tentacles STR+1D, Move 105/300 kph, 300m long — voracious, attacks floater sharks and ships alike; target the gasbag to force descent). All three creature types are in the Creature Lookup. Corusca gems harvested here are among the most valuable minerals in the galaxy. The Rebel Alliance's Yavin 4 base used the gas giant's gravity shadow during the Death Star approach."
