    majorImports: "Mid technology; unofficial imports include all manner of illegal goods and weapons technology",
    source: "WEG40075 Galaxy Guide 11: Criminal Organizations p.14, 17, 72-74",
    summary: "Originally founded by a subsidiary of Gesenix Mining, Andasala started out as a promising community with natural resources and a favorable position for servicing numerous nearby systems. Lying not far from Svivren, it quickly expanded its population and economy. With the coming of the New Republic, however, Andasala's location became a handicap — both Imperial and New Republic forces used the system as a corridor through which other targets could be attacked. The latest clash saw the Empire reclaim Andasala after all but eliminating the New Republic garrison in a massive orbital bombardment. Recent events in the Imperial Civil War left Andasala without a planetary governor, and into this power vacuum came local crimelord Valis Lorn, who used his criminal connections to finance a successful political campaign and establish himself as Provisional Governor.",
    locations: "Ranis quarter (controlled by enforcer Ughok Snorg). Garimor Street. Numerous Hutt-operated gambling palaces, bookmaker shops, export houses fronting for professional thieves, credit laundering banks, and establishments catering to other vices.",
    ofNote: "Home of the Valis Lorn cartel. Lorn declared Andasala an 'open planet' where Imperial and Republic citizens alike can come and go, provided they leave political squabbling at home. He contracted with the Mantis Syndicate for a company of mercenaries as 'peacekeepers' and bought off nearby Imperial officials with large donations. The Hutts have been invited in by Lorn to provide additional off-world credits, bringing gambling palaces, loan sharks, con men, and informants. Native Andasalan gangs are increasingly hostile to the Hutt presence, and many citizens are rallying to their local crime bosses to resist. Lorn sits atop this volatile situation with calculated complacency, playing the Hutts against the native gangs. Children are subjected to mandatory classroom instruction glorifying Lorn's role as planetary saviour. The Ranis quarter is overseen by Gamorrean enforcer Ughok Snorg. Premier loan shark Sires Vant also operates here."
