    summary: "Known as the forbidden planet, Gesaril is covered with an incredibly thick jungle that actually floats above a noxious swamp. It is inhabited by the Gesarils — small, heavily-furred, six-limbed, hyperactive creatures with a strange affinity for the Force. All Gesarils possess the Force skill Sense at 1D, are highly sensitive to emotion, and greatly fear anger and aggression. When the Empire's scouts first landed and treated the natives harshly, the Gesarils are believed to have combined their powers to crash the scout ship on takeoff and later dragged other ships out of orbit — nine Imperial ships have crashed on the same coastal section. The planet is now under strict Imperial quarantine. The Gesarils are friendly with visitors who are not fearful or aggressive but extremely skittish around those who are moody or violent. They are excellent carvers who imbue their wooden masks and statues with psychic energy — anyone holding a carving can feel the emotion the crafter felt while making it.",
