    source: "WEG40095 Galaxy Guide 6: Tramp Freighters p.64",
    summary: "Travnin is a desolate, wind-swept moon circling a gas giant — the only planet in its double-star system. The terrain is extremely rugged and nearly barren of life. It serves as the Imperial administrative hub for the Minos Cluster, housing the regional offices of the Empire, the HQ for the Imperial Fleet of the Cluster, and the residence of the reclusive Moff. The Human population exists solely because of the Imperial base, brought in long ago to manage galactic affairs. Nearly everyone works for the Empire as clerks, stevedores, navy personnel, or entertainers. The planet has been in dire straits as the Empire reduces its presence in the Cluster, with nearly one-third of the population losing their jobs. The natives are corrupt and servile to their superiors, terrified of the Empire they serve, and nearly universally disliked across the Cluster.",
    locations: "Starport and surrounding city (only city of note). Towns along the small ocean (~300 km from the city). The Grand Design (famous spacers' bar — circular revolving building where everything inside rotates, booths, tables, holo screens, drink glasses, and certain chairs all spin; spacer folk only). The Arena (ruined swoop racing arena — collapsed during opening ceremonies due to flimsy construction from Imperial corruption; substantial tunnel network beneath now houses the planet's underworld and black market). Imperial Fleet HQ. Moff's residence.",
    ofNote: "First habitable rock into the Minos Cluster — gateway system. Imperial class starport with heavy presence. The Arena's tunnel maze is where all illegal trade and shady business happens. The Grand Design bar is the best place to openly trade information and make contacts. Nearly one-third of population unemployed due to Imperial drawdown. Supplies the Gesaril prison asteroid (100 tons every 50 days). The population suspects they've 'sold their souls' to evil but are too fearful to act. Imperial officials across the Cluster come from Travnin."
