    summary: "Known as the Twin Planets, Shesharile 5 and 6 are two heavily-settled, industrial moons circling the same gas giant, ruled by one system-wide government. Both moons are thickly overlaid with outdated industry and impossible to escape the filth and pollution — these are garbage planets. In their headlong pursuit of wealth, the people ruined their environment but became so accustomed to filth that no one notices. The system's economy was built on Imperial military contracts, and when the Empire pulled out (diverting funds to the new Death Star), Shesharile plunged into the worst depression the Cluster has ever seen. Prices doubled virtually every day, local credits fell to one-fiftieth face value, and organized crime began taking control of the cities. The largest city on Shesharile 6 is completely ruled by crime boss Yerkys ne Dago.",
    locations: "Spaceport (extremely tough customs — bribes required at every level or delays of weeks/months). Industrial zones across both moons. Resorts on Shesharile 5 (for the very rich, but still dirty by galactic standards). Minos-Mestra Corporation main headquarters (on Shesharile 5). Cities on Shesharile 6 (largest controlled by Yerkys ne Dago).",
    ofNote: "Narco-spice is a major problem and leading export, popular on Travnin and Adarlon as well. Spicerunners are everywhere. Customs is entirely local officials — bribes needed for inspectors, laborers, truckers, everyone. The economic collapse creates opportunity: cargo can become instantly worthless, but credits can still be made if you know where to look. The depression is unlikely to spread to other Cluster worlds since most exports went to Imperial military. A defunct munitions plant could theoretically produce for the Rebellion. Street gangs are paid by city governments to keep order and in many cases control the governments themselves."
