    ofNote: "Home of the Slaver Syndicate — a bounty hunter syndicate that captures less-wanted fugitives, collects their bounties, then buys ownership rights and sells them as slaves instead of handing them to the Empire for imprisonment. Alien species such as Agorffi, Gamorreans, and Wookiees are particularly prized for brawn and hard labor. One of three major slaving hubs in the Outer Rim (with Zygeria and the Thalassian system). Also home to the Karazak Slavers' Cooperative (KSC) — an estimated 12,000+ members, over 5,000 directly engaged in strike team operations. The KSC is organized into specialized roles: acquisitions specialists (scouts), project developers (raid planners), strike team leaders, logistics coordinators, and distribution managers. No member is allowed to remain incarcerated for more than 30 hours — the guild covers all legal expenses and bribes, or sends tactical initiative squads. Families of killed members are provided for without question. Operations extend into both Imperial and New Republic sectors, focusing on trained and literate captures with an emphasis on high-risk/high-fee private commissions. A few local chapters have Hutt-funded support elements."
