    summary: "Kallistas is an inhospitable desert world with little to offer except radioactives and native gems in the craggy hills of its northern hemisphere. A colony world established in the early years of Governor Linrec's administration, Kallistas is now nearly forgotten and subject to periodic Rebel incursions that have forced most of the settlers to leave.",
    locations: "Trevalis (pop. 220, main settlement) — administration building with Prefect's office, detention center, militia barracks, and central computer complex; spaceport landing field (fenced open desert); customs office with subspace radio; warehouses storing mining lasers and power generators; community support building with dining room, holotheater, tavern, market, and public communications center; central security storage for gems and radioactives. Mindori (pop. ~70, northern mining town) — assay office coordinating gem production; militia post; emergency hospital with FX medical droids; open mining pits up to 200m across and 50m deep; oasis and native fruit grove; water reservoir and moisture reclamation plant; public meeting house and library. Vexen (pop. ~100, radioactives mining center) — town hall with mining administration and communications; decontamination center; militia post; radioactives mine extending deep under a mountain; containment sheds for ore processing and shipment. Galas (abandoned gem mine settlement, ruins frequented by sand bears).",
    ofNote: "Now home to pirates, smugglers, and other assorted ne'er-do-wells who prey on local shipping and the occasional Imperial freighter. Population has dwindled to just 452 due to Rebel incursions and Imperial neglect. Prefect Dengless Rinn governs from Trevalis and is secretly plotting with Twi'lek smuggler Tarquin Zian and the Mantis Syndicate to trade illicit Kallistan gems for weapons and mercenaries, with a hidden refinery northeast of Trevalis processing radioactives into bomb material. Pirate captain Jondrell Inx is a native Kallistan who funnels credits back to the communities and is regarded fondly by locals. Rebel agent Pallas Quintell operates a hidden underground base camp in the northern foothills with a communications center and armory. A hidden Rebel arms cache is stored in an unused section of the Vexen radioactives mine. Governor Linrec's daughter Cressis has gone missing on-world. Sand bears are the only known carnivore — solitary nocturnal ambush predators that move silently beneath the sand."
