    majorImports: "Shipped cargoes, tourism",
    source: "WEG40131 The Thrawn Trilogy Sourcebook p.108",
    summary: "Berchest is one of the larger trade worlds in Anthos sector, situated well behind Imperial lines. Despite its proximity to Imperial rule, a thriving illicit smuggling trade has flourished there. Rather than travel from remote Outer Rim bases, many smugglers find it useful to have a staging area near their prospective markets. Anthos sector contains a number of systems ideal for smugglers, as a planetary collision thousands of years ago left an unusually high frequency of radioactive and sensor-fouling material on or near many of the major trade routes. Since the very early days of the Old Republic, Berchest has been hailed as a planet of extraordinary beauty. Its seas — in particular the magnificent red-orange sprawl of the Leefari Sea — are composed of a particularly strong saline solution. Powered by the strong tides created by Terhaari (Berchest's sole moon), the seas have had a profound effect on the rocky planet, creating huge crystal deposits on the shores, sometimes several kilometers in diameter. These crystals have been painstakingly carved into actual cities by Berchestian artisans — 'citysculpting' is a highly respected and cherished art form.",
    locations: "Calius Saj Leeloo (City of Glowing Crystal; premier tourist attraction; carefully carved from the planet's largest crystal deposit; at sunset the crystal city shines with otherworldly brilliance, radiating a deep red hue renowned throughout the galaxy). Sanctum Arcti (gathering house for the Berchestian world-religion; stands almost a full kilometer tall and covers nearly three square kilometers; virtually every centimeter of its surface is elegantly sculpted; positioned for maximum sun exposure with special tinting to subtly alter coloration; houses over 2,000 scholars and artisans constantly planning and overseeing new architectural sculpture designs). Leefari Sea (magnificent red-orange saline sea; tidal forces from moon Terhaari create the crystal deposits).",
    ofNote: "Currently under the rule of Imperial Governor Raccyx Staffa, a former smuggler who conned his way into power. The Clone Wars and the Empire severely cut into Berchest's tourist trade, forcing the Berchestians to find alternative income through trade routes established during better times. A large amount of off-world traffic passes through Berchest, monitored by the Empire. During the New Republic's search for Imperial clone traffic, Berchest was one of many false shipping routes Thrawn used to keep his enemies occupied. Imperial troops patrol the city of Calius regularly. The Berchestians espouse no particular political view, preferring peace and free trade — after all, many of their best customers are not Imperials."
