    summary: "Elom is a cold, barren world, a sort of frozen desert far from its system's sun. Rich in mineral resources, especially an ore called lommite, the planet's discovery was hailed as a major find by the Senate's exploration council in the days of the Old Republic. Like the world of Calamari, Elom joined the Rebel Alliance to combat the tyranny of the Empire and to free itself from enslavement. Also like the Mon Cals, Elomin tend to serve in units of their own species — whole ships are often crewed and captained by nothing but Elomin. The Elomin have been busy rebuilding their economy and culture since casting off the Empire.",
    locations: "",
    ofNote: "Elom's proximity to the Borderland Regions leaves the Elomin fearful that they will again face oppression and enslavement. The planet has been engaged in a massive armament program since gaining freedom. | WANTED — LAERRON WOERN: New Republic bounty of 25,000 credits plus an additional 10,000 credits from the Elomin Council (total: 35,000). Wanted alive. Charges: piracy, theft. Elomin pirate fleet commander with over 100 soldiers and several assault ships. His last eight strikes have targeted the New Republic specifically. Last seen in the Atrig system on Korbin, suspected of purchasing New Republic trade route information from government spies. His actions are considered a disgrace by the Elomin people. | CRACKEN'S PERSONAL NOTES: Piracy is a crime for which I have very little tolerance. It is theft and terrorism at its most base level. This kind of individual represents a grave threat to the Republic — we have achieved nothing if our people cannot travel the star lanes without fear of being attacked and robbed. Of course, during the difficult times of the war against the Empire, we resorted to theft on many occasions. However, our raids were confined to Imperial ships or corporate vessels solidly pledged to the Empire, and even then, we concentrated on making the raids as bloodless as possible."
