    summary: "Farrfin was a popular refuge of smugglers and pirates in the days of the Old Republic. Its remote location made it ideal for hiding from pursuers, and eventually the Rebel Alliance made use of the planet as well. The Farghul, a species easily given to smuggling and con artistry, freely welcomed all newcomers — if only for the chance to bilk the unwary out of every credit they could. The planet is medium-sized with high mountain peaks, deep valleys, some tectonic instability, and underground streams. These streams meet with lava just beneath the surface, causing huge fissures of steam to explode from the ground. These 'steam storms' make the planet difficult for the Empire to cope with: the damp weather, low visibility, and treacherous terrain have all contributed to making Imperial occupation extremely difficult.",
