    summary: "Nestled atop a tight ring of wroshyr trees, Rwookrrorro stands as one of Kashyyyk's most beautiful metropolitan centers. It hangs as though suspended in mid-air, filling the gaps between the massive trees. A true city covering more than a square kilometer, its multi-leveled buildings are large and complex, laid out in wide, straight avenues. The combination of architecture and planning demonstrates a loving sense of artistry — the trunks form giant brown columns around and within the city, reaching up to support the ceiling of white clouds overhead. Unlike Cloud City, Rwookrrorro is held aloft only by incredibly strong branches of Kashyyyk's trees.",
    locations: "Landing Platforms (remnants of huge tree limbs cut horizontally close to the trunk; accommodate speeders and medium-sized cruisers). Houses, shops, and buildings (many built directly into the trees, entrances open to empty space — only Wookiee climbing claws allow natural access). Liftcars (cargo and transport for the ill; ferried up and down by dark green kshyy vines, stronger than composite cables and self-repairing; equipped with emergency repulsor units).",
    ofNote: "Wroshyr tree branches have a unique property: when separate branches meet, they grow together to form one interlocked branch, which then sprouts new branches reaching out to join with others. All wroshyr trees in the Rwookrrorro grouping are a single giant plant with a unified, intermixed root system — in that unity, the plant grows stronger. The sweeping lights around the city do more than guide ships — they attract kroyie birds so city hunters can catch them, making up a large portion of the Wookiee diet. Most Wookiees prefer to get around naturally by climbing rather than using liftcars."
