    summary: "Most people know Ord Mantell as a gambling reserve and seedy spacer and smuggler conclave, but there's more to this outlying world. Originally founded by Corellian colonists 12,000 years ago as an advance Republic military and scout base ('Ord' stands for Ordnance/Regional Depot). As the Republic expanded to new trade routes, Ord Mantell lost strategic significance, but the presence of full military-quality starship yards encouraged a thriving civilian cargo trade. In the intervening years, it has become a 'free port' — all manner of legitimate and illegal cargoes pass through the system.",
    locations: "Worlport Southern Coast (sprawl of cities providing gambling and all manner of vices, no questions asked; modern in all respects with any convenience tourists expect from the Core). Rural Spacer Cities (little more than outlaw settlements like Mos Eisley, where visitors must dispense justice through a threatening word and a blaster). Ord Mantell Fighter Wing Base (remains of an Old Republic space defense base in the southern hemisphere; now houses a New Republic X-wing fighter wing).",
    ofNote: "Ord Mantell has a thriving gambling and entertainment industry with countless billions of tourists per year. Beyond the teeming cities, much of the planet remains primitive and rural — droids and computers are oddities to most rural residents. The New Republic has made extensive efforts to 'civilize' the planet, but old habits die hard. The Republic deployed an X-wing fighter wing to assist in ongoing sector skirmishes. Smugglers and legal free traders dock confidently, knowing there is minimal risk of Imperial entanglements."
