    ofNote: "The H'kig religion was founded by a religious leader on the Core World of Galand who was martyred for preaching against the Viceroy. After centuries of persecution, his followers colonized Rishi. The theocratic government has established laws based on religious beliefs — specific laws forbid repulsorlifts before first meal and after last prayer. Strict standards of propriety concerning clothing, hair length, and social mores apply in public. First offenses get a warning and small fine; multiple offenders may be banished; capital crimes (murder, kidnapping, grand theft) can carry death sentences. The colonists remain neutral in the Imperial/NR conflict and allow anyone to trade fairly with them. Many underworld organizations have established bases here because of this tolerance. Bounty hunters followed Karrde to Rishi seeking a huge Thrawn-decreed bounty; most left empty-handed."
