    ofNote: "Protected by a minimum of two Imperial-class Star Destroyers and 10 to 50 smaller vessels (Carrack-class light cruisers, Interdictor cruisers, Victory-class Star Destroyers). Imperial officers joke that anything entering the system without authorization — including space debris — is destroyed without even a comm warning. A complex series of remote sensors ensures nothing enters undetected. The maze-like surface canyons are monitored by motion trackers, heat sensors, and sentry posts. Tangrene was once home to peaceful nomads enslaved by the Empire to construct garrison bases and shield generators. After construction was completed, the sector Moff decided to depopulate the planet rather than risk revolt — the Tangrene people were completely wiped out. The Empire has recently upgraded shield generators, and Tangrene has become an increasingly attractive staging area for Imperial incursions into Republic space."
