    summary: "Tierfon hosts a hidden Rebel Alliance starfighter outpost established to patrol the outer Sumitra sector, escort secret transports, and refuel ships on long-range intelligence missions. Rebel scouts selected a site in a cliff face overlooking a huge valley, providing safe flight paths shielded naturally by the cliff. Engineers blasted a cave over 250 meters deep into solid rock, built interior walls of permacite and shaped formex, reinforced critical areas with metal core and epoxy armor. All piping and wiring is surface-mounted for immediate access.",
    locations: "Hangars (each shelters one starfighter with computer/navigation ground links, cold engine starters, external power, overhead winches and lifts; 'Ready One' position always flight-ready, scramble in one minute). Armory (heavily armored vault for missiles, bombs, detonators, replacement laser actuators and barrels, heavy ground weapons). Medical Suite (diagnostic sensors, medical computers, surgical theater, bacta rejuve tank; staffed by one surgeon and two medical droids MD-1 and MD-2; six bed patients, overflow in adjacent cabins). Command Center (communications, sensors, above-ground array, secret remote units, picket ships feed data; holographic projector for 3D composite briefing images; controls power generators, life support, shields). Standard Cabins (4-12 Rebels per cabin, hand-made bunks to salvaged pre-fab units). Staterooms (officers only; double as offices, labs, briefing rooms, microcircuitry shops). Common Room (mess hall, recreation area, lounge, briefing room, fitness center, transit barracks). Galley (walk-in freezers, dry-food lockers, compact equipment from passenger ship galleys). Storage (bags of dry formex to delicate droid parts; special vaults for perishables). Control Tower (primary lookout, tracks all atmospheric and ground movement in 1,000 km radius, directs laser fire and ground strikes during attack; armored, supports primary communication antennas). Observation Towers (concealed, manned by lookouts with macrobinoculars, low-frequency comlinks). Fuel Cells (high-energy capacitors for recharging starfighters and defensive laser cannons; supplement shield power generators during bombardment).",
    ofNote: "0 BBY/ABY (early Rebellion era). Personnel: 18 pilots, 54 ground troops (including laser turret crews), 8 command staff, 8 X-wing ground crew chiefs, 24 ground crew technicians, 18 junior staff, 24 general staff (158 total). Vehicles: 5 airspeeders, 2 landspeeders, 4 speeder bikes, 8 X-wing starfighters, plus hangar space for 1 shuttle or stock light freighter (19 total). Pilots maintain strict radio silence; coded emergency messages less than one second. Life support is hand-built and deliberately run below full capacity to avoid energy signatures that might alert Imperial sensors. Repulsorlift elevators connect underground base to above-ground facilities; lift shafts include ladder rungs and can be collapsed with special charges if infiltrated. Crash wagon (repulsorlift tractor with blast shield) used for hangar emergencies and above-ground excavation. Located in Sumitra sector — local Imperials may suspect a Rebel outpost exists but face searching 12,387 planets and moons to find it. If discovered, could not withstand a determined Imperial assault."
