    summary: "Alpheridies orbits Aber, a red dwarf star that emits little visible light but enough infrared radiation to maintain a habitable atmosphere. Most of the planet's native fauna lack visual sense organs entirely, relying on sound, smell, touch, and infrared reception to navigate their environment. Several thousand years ago, Miralukan scouts discovered Alpheridies while searching for a new homeworld after their original planet suffered catastrophic geophysical and geochemical instability. Though not a perfect match, it met most of their requirements and the entire Miralukan population migrated here. Their governing council unanimously resolved that this world would not be exploited as their previous home had been — only a handful of population centers were permitted to operate light industry while the vast majority of Miraluka turned to agricultural life. Over millennia the Miraluka gradually lost the use of their eyes in the dim light of Aber, but a long-dormant gene simultaneously reemerged granting the species the ability to sense the Force vibrations emitted by all living things.",
    locations: "Population centers (small industrial settlements producing computers, repulsorlift parts, and farming equipment — the only areas with information-level technology). Agricultural communities (cooperative farming settlements spread across the hills and plains). Rumored Sith citadel (a hidden underground fortress supposedly built by an ancient Sith warlord who used Alpheridies as a base when this region was considered Unknown Space; said to contain dark side artifacts, texts, and other relics; location unconfirmed by any official source).",
    ofNote: "4000 BBY (Tales of the Jedi era). The Miraluka are a Near-Human species who perceive the world entirely through the Force — born without functional eyes, they rely on a species-wide form of Force sight to navigate their environment. This ability is not considered unusual among Miraluka. The Miralukan migration to Alpheridies occurred several thousand years before 4000 BBY. Rumors persist of a buried Sith stronghold somewhere in the planet's subterranean depths, though the Miraluka officially deny any knowledge of it. The system is also referred to as the Abron system in some records, with the star designated Aber."
