    source: "WEG40114 The Jedi Academy Sourcebook p.111",
    summary: "A colony world in the Anoat system with a history of ambition crushed by the Empire. Over two generations, a fish-farming cooperative of thousands of families transformed vast swampland into a complex of terraformed lakes, maintaining them with aquifer plants and stocking them with commercially valuable fish. Rather than build on the remaining swamp, the colonists constructed raft cities on the lakes, linked by canals that transported fish to packing plants near Feiya — the only landbased township and the site of the spaceport. Shipments traveled up the Ison Corridor to Bespin and the Corellian Trade Spine. Proud of their economic success, the colonists adapted their co-op charter to model Old Republic democracy, intending to demonstrate that self-governance worked on a small scale. Emperor Palpatine tolerated the experiment until they voted to denounce the destruction of Alderaan and demand repeal of the New Order; he had the colony overrun and its people scattered to penal centers. The co-op collapsed, the fish died, and the canals filled with weeds. Now a backwater of squatters, criminals, and survivors clinging to the moldering ruins.",
    locations: "Feiya (the only landbased township; site of the spaceport and the fish-packing plants that routed product up the Ison Corridor). Canal network and raft cities (formerly linked the lake settlements, now decaying; few venture beyond Feiya).",
    ofNote: "In the Anoat system (same grid as Anoat). The colonists' democratic experiment — modeled on the Old Republic charter — was the direct cause of Imperial retribution. 14 ABY STATUS: Effectively a lawless backwater; small community of squatters and survivors, mostly near Feiya."
