    source: "WEG40114 The Jedi Academy Sourcebook pp.113–115",
    summary: "The capital of Umgul, built on a series of slight hills above a flat central plain bisected by a large, sluggish river, with steep limestone bluffs breaking the surrounding flatlands. Wisps of mist constantly rise from the river and sweep across the plain, often leaving only the hilltops above the fog — creating the appearance of a series of urban islands in an ethereal sea. The cityscape is densely built with blockish multi-story limestone buildings lacquered to a high gloss with moisture sealants, streetlights hung from cables along cobblestoned streets, and banners and posters everywhere advertising upcoming celebrity visits and gala events. The commercial orbital and landing vectors are thick with tourist traffic — private ships, space yachts, luxury starliners, sail barges, ground skimmers, zeppelins, and airspeeders.",
    locations: "Umgul Spaceport (on limestone plateau bluffs above the river; many landing bays carved into underground caverns in the cliffs; main concourse is chaotic — laughing tourists, Ugnaught trinket vendors, loud holographic attraction displays; premium first-class gates maintained by security for those wanting to avoid the crowd). Commutube system (Umgul's mass-transit magrail; travels at high speed, ducking underground beneath the river and congested districts, running at grade elsewhere, and soaring onto elevated rails hundreds of meters above the city; connects all major tourist destinations). Fondine Blob Raceways (on a bluff east of town; served by the dedicated Raceway Line commutube branch, lined with garish billboards and gambling-loan advertisements; blob race coverage broadcast within the tube cars in multiple languages; see Umgul planet entry for full description).",
