    aliases: ["Evocar"],
    source: "WEG40071 Dark Empire Sourcebook p.89",
    summary: "Nal Hutta, meaning 'Glorious Jewel' in Huttese, is the adopted homeworld of the Hutts after they fled Varl, their original world which was destroyed when one of its two suns crashed into a black hole. The Hutts claimed Evocar, the largest planet in the Y'Toub system, as their new homeworld. Despite its huge size, Evocar had an extremely low density with almost no heavy metals, making its gravity comparable to a standard world. It was originally home to the Evocii, a species of humanoids in a primitive feudal state of development. The Hutts offered to sell the Evocii modern technology, trading it for real estate — the Evocii never suspected the Hutts were trying to buy the planet out from under them. By the time they learned what the Hutts were up to, construction teams had already begun arriving. The Evocii appealed to the Republic, but even a Jedi couldn't find a loophole in a Hutt contract. The Evocii were relocated to a nearby moon. The ancient monuments were replaced with Hutt shrines and the planet was renamed Nal Hutta. The late Jabba himself was born here on the private estates of his family. Though the planet is owned by Hutts and according to tradition Huttese is the only language permitted to be spoken here, there are many non-Hutt residents as part of the enormous class of slaves, servants and sycophants found wherever Hutts reside. From here they control the entire economic life of their moon, Nar Shaddaa, an ancient spacer's base and home to many of the pilots and techs working for the Hutt smuggling guilds.",
