    source: "WEG40029 The Far Orbit Project p.62",
    summary: "Darpa sector capital and the secure home of Imperial power in the area. The population clings to a parochial 'Esseles first' ideology with only lukewarm interest in the Empire's High Culture ideology, but the New Order party is firmly in control of the Esselian Hall. A brisk manufacturing economy with dozens of corporate branches represented.",
    locations: "Terril Naval Base (the sector's major military installation — the only facility in Darpa sector equipped to handle Star Destroyers). Esselian Hall (seat of planetary government).",
    ofNote: "GOVERNMENT: The lingering remains of Esselian power lie primarily in the hands of President Cambira Ralle, an aging Clone Wars veteran who never opposes Palpatine's edicts and is essentially powerless. Moff Graffe's official residence is here. Imperial Governor Griff Takel is a moderate and capable administrator, balancing Imperial demands with Esselian sensibilities. Both Graffe and Takel work to ensure Esselian loyalty via pro-Imperial marches, rallies, and 'spontaneous' pro-Palpatine demonstrations. | INDUSTRY: Although no major manufacturers are headquartered on Esseles, most Bormea sector corporations have production facilities here to take advantage of the concentration of engineers and favorable tax base. Aether Hypernautics, Sienar Fleet Systems, Les Tech, and Gowix Computers all have important factories here. | MILITARY: Sector capital with deep Imperial investment. Esseles naval bases directly command the two Darpa sector border outposts (2LC/Blue and 1B6/Green) near the Ringali Nebula."
