    ofNote: "OCCUPATION: Moff Jander Graffe used a trumped-up charge of rebellion to justify a full-scale invasion led by Lord Tion. An entire line corps is assigned — Army troopers and stormtroopers patrol the streets. Travel requires a transit pass, arrests for political crimes are common, and a strict curfew is enforced. Lord Tion has turned over the occupation to Imperial Governor Dennix Graeber, a harsh sadist and protege of Moff Graffe. | FINANCIAL COLLAPSE: The Ralltiiran banking system is in shambles. The majority of banking assets are frozen by the Empire pending investigation. Show trials are expected, with non-human accounts seized, interest confiscated, and human accounts released only to supporters of Imperial policies. Interstellar corporations are departing rapidly, but citizens cannot leave without expensive and difficult-to-acquire travel visas. | MILITARY PRESENCE: The system is patrolled by a superiority force — three battle squadrons and a light squadron, including three Imperial Star Destroyers and the VSD Scourge. Space around Ralltiir is highly restricted; chances of encountering heavily-armed military convoys or patrol ships are tripled. The ruling High Council remains in place but has been purged of all political 'unreliables.'"
