    summary: "Homeworld of the Advozse, including Bom Vimdin — a smuggler repeatedly caught transporting Imperial agents from New Republic territories to Imperial-controlled space. Despite multiple captures, Vimdin has always gained release through the intervention of unknown agents.",
    locations: "",
    ofNote: "WANTED — BOM VIMDIN: New Republic bounty of 12,000 credits. Wanted alive. Charges: smuggling, treason, aiding Imperial forces. Vimdin has been caught multiple times transporting Imperial agents but always gains release with outside help from unknown agents. Commander Solo confirms Vimdin is among the best at what he does. His wealth enables him to hire extremely loyal operatives. Flies a stock Ghtroc freighter. | CRACKEN'S PERSONAL NOTES: Bom Vimdin is a true mercenary: one who would sell his soul, the fate of his people, and even that of the galaxy for a few credits. He cares little for what happens to those he harms provided the credit balance in his account grows. In all the times that Vimdin has been captured and later freed, there is no information at all regarding those agents who work for him."
