    summary: "Homeworld of the Sullustans, including Gaor Tembon — a smuggler of wide renown in the Borderland Regions. Tembon has worked for the Empire, the Hutt crime families, and the Riders of the Maelstrom, and has even participated in slave running operations.",
    locations: "",
    ofNote: "WANTED — GAOR TEMBON: New Republic bounty of 30,000 credits. Wanted alive. Charges: smuggling, transportation of slaves, conspiracy to deprive sapients of their freedom, manslaughter. Tembon has never been personally caught. His operatives claim he has changed his ways — cutting off all relations with the Empire and refusing slave cargoes after the Empire attempted to forcibly seize his ships. He has reportedly sworn to help overthrow the Empire. Current location believed to be the Nexer system, close to main trade routes but far from inquiring officials. Flies a Miv'rah Firestorm freighter. | CRACKEN'S PERSONAL NOTES: Gaor Tembon represents an interesting case. Though it is without question that he has committed atrocities, his recent actions have been of great help to us. However, I cannot condone the activities of a former slaver — despite his seeming 'change of face,' he must be brought to justice!"
