    summary: "Homeworld of Beyla Rus, the 'Gentleman Pirate,' who commands a Corellian Corvette with a crew of roughly 60 cutthroats and scoundrels. Known for his no-kill policy — his pirates use stun weapons and shrewd tactics, leaving victims alive to spread tales of his audacity.",
    locations: "",
    ofNote: "WANTED — BEYLA RUS: New Republic bounty of 15,000 credits. Wanted alive. Charges: theft, piracy, destruction of New Republic property. Rus targets primarily merchant ships and New Republic cargo vessels from his Corellian Corvette. His pirates never kill — they use stun weapons and prefer victims alive to spread tales of their exploits. During the Rebellion he was careful not to anger either side. Can potentially be lured with rumors of a suitably valuable cargo. | CRACKEN'S PERSONAL NOTES: Despite his piracy, it is difficult to truly hate Rus, who at least operates with some style. He is smug, overconfident and roguish. He is a pirate more for the sport of it than the material gain, and his bloodless record is a point in his favor. But the fact remains that he is a threat to New Republic commerce, at a time when the fledgling union of worlds cannot afford that. Bringing Rus to justice would be an example to other pirates that such activities will not be tolerated."
