    techLevel: "Space",
    source: "WEG40062 Wanted by Cracken p.43",
    summary: "Seltaya is a frigid, icy world in the Outer Rim that serves as the hidden base of the pirate captain Pendon. Pendon's band consists of approximately 200 pirates of numerous species. While many pirates plunder ships and keep the stolen goods, Pendon sells the majority of his merchandise to a wide variety of clients. During the Empire's reign, Pendon dealt only with criminal organizations and, on rare occasion, the Rebel Alliance. Since the rise of the New Republic, Pendon no longer deals with them since his activities are now unacceptable. However, since turnabout is fair play, Pendon now sells to the Empire along with his usual clientele of smugglers and crime lords.",
    locations: "Pendon's Base (located in a large mountain range in the northern polar region of Seltaya, built within a large network of caves discovered after a botched pirate raid on an Imperial convoy forced Pendon to land on the ice planet; the base has been expanded and reinforced into a formidable stronghold). Level 1 — Hangar Bay (located nearest to the surface, enormous enough to hold Pendon's entire fleet of starfighters, small freighters, Corellian corvettes, gunships, Imperial blastboats, and transports; also houses ship maintenance and repair facilities with a cargo lift to lower maintenance and storage areas). Level 2 — Operations Level (houses operations and planning rooms, training and workout facilities, the treasure vault where Pendon keeps stolen merchandise, communications and sensor room with targeting systems for the KDY v-150 Planet Defender Ion Cannon). Level 3 — Living Quarters (bottom level with military-style bunk rooms featuring cots with wrap-around privacy curtains and small storage cabinets; Pendon and his top aides have personal suites).",
    ofNote: "KDY v-150 PLANET DEFENDER ION CANNON: Positioned nearly 100 kilometers south of the base, similar to the one used by the Rebel Alliance on Hoth. Used to cripple undesirable ships that wander too close to Seltaya. Several rotating shifts of crewmen operate the gun. | SENSOR NETWORK: After establishing the base, Pendon positioned several ground-based sensors on the planet's surface along with several orbital sensor satellites to detect any incoming ship as it approaches. These sensors warn Pendon and his pirates of any unexpected visitors. | PENDON'S FLEET: Includes starfighters, small freighters, several Corellian corvettes and gunships, as well as Imperial blastboats and transports. This broad combination provides the firepower needed for attacking New Republic convoys. | AVERAGE PIRATE: The pirates come from a variety of backgrounds. Many served other leaders until they elected to join Pendon. Stats: DEX 2D+2 (blaster 3D+2, dodge 4D, melee combat 5D, melee parry 4D), KNO 2D (streetwise 3D+2, survival 3D), MEC 2D+2 (astrogation 3D+2, repulsorlift operation 3D+2, starfighter piloting 4D, starship gunnery 4D, starship shields 3D), PER 3D (hide 4D+2, search 4D, sneak 4D), STR 2D+2 (brawling 4D, stamina 5D), TEC 3D (security 4D). Force Points: 0. Character Points: 0-5. Equipment: Blaster pistol (4D damage)."
