    source: "WEG40062 Wanted by Cracken pp.62-63",
    summary: "Shalm is a primitive frontier world in the Outer Rim that was conquered by the Empire. As the Empire was forced to retreat, this relatively unimportant world was abandoned. The abandoned Imperial garrison on the western side of Mount Ganton, overlooking the valley of the capital city of Hondan, is now the base of operations for Kolor Delan's mercenary group, Pendarran's Revenge. The people of Shalm have learned to leave the Imperials alone, so even though the garrison is now occupied by a mercenary army, the locals believe it is still held by the invaders who once took over and then retreated without warning.",
    locations: "Hondan (capital city in the valley below Mount Ganton). Abandoned Imperial Garrison (steep cliff face on western side of Mount Ganton, northern continent, Ganton mountain region; once housed thousands, now home to Delan's army numbering in the hundreds; exceptional facilities, well-stocked arsenal, and many combat vehicles).",
    ofNote: "GARRISON DEFENSES: Set high on a mountain, difficult to approach undetected. Numerous sensor beacons around the base of the mountain. 10-meter tall high-voltage 'death fence' at mountain base with two gates (north and south ends), no catwalk along perimeter. Four heavy turbolaser emplacements on garrison and mountaintop (5D Walker-scale damage). | IMPERIAL EQUIPMENT LEFT BEHIND: 20 TIE fighters, 5 AT-AT walkers, 10 AT-STs, 25 speeder bikes, 15 landspeeders, 5 hoverscouts, 10 command speeders, 10 Compact Assault Vehicles, 2 Floating Fortresses, 1 Mobile Command Base, 2 Lambda-class shuttles. Arsenal includes 300+ Imperial blaster pistols, blaster rifles, heavy blaster rifles, thermal detonators, and artillery pieces — enough gear for over 200 troops with comlinks, survival gear, and other items. | PENDARRAN'S REVENGE FLEET: 3 light freighters, 3 captured Skipray blastboats, 2 heavy transports, and 20 starfighters of various makes including 5 Zebras, 3 Gauntlets, 2 captured TIE Interceptors, and 5 rebuilt X-wings (bought from salvage yards)."
