    techLevel: "Feudal/Space",
    majorExports: "Mid- and high-technology",
    majorImports: "Metals, minerals",
    source: "WEG40083 Classic Adventures p.93",
    summary: "Narg is a low-tech world quickly industrialized by the Empire to strip it of natural resources. Discovered by the Imperial Survey Corps less than five standard years ago, the Rayter Sector Resource Analysis Committee decided the inhabitants — humans living in an agrarian society — were not advanced enough to deserve equal status. Narg was annexed as a provisional protectorate under TransGalMeg Industries, Inc., which was given full executive powers over the planet's resources for a ten-year period. Heavy industry fueled by local coal is centralized in four major cities in the northern temperate zone. Most inhabitants have been unwillingly relocated due to appropriation of their farmlands.",
    locations: "",
    ofNote: "The natives are xenophobic, having only recently been exposed to aliens. TransGalMeg prefers to employ only humans. Rural residents eschew technology and try to pretend the cities do not exist. The people do not understand the technology surrounding them — under stress they are more likely to run into traffic than board a hoverbus, or quench a fire with water than with a halogen cylinder. TransGalMeg is determined to extract as much from the planet as possible before their sponsorship concludes."
