    starport: "2 Limited services",
    population: "3,500 Humans, 50,000 Morodins (estimated)",
    function: "Abandoned colony, subsistence",
    government: "Participatory democracy",
    techLevel: "Space (around starports), feudal",
    majorExports: "None",
    majorImports: "Foodstuffs, high technology, medicinal goods",
    source: "WEG40129 Adventure Journal 1 p.20",
    summary: "Varonat was settled 250 years ago by idealists from Salliche led by the charismatic ex-legislator Adarian Tropis, who was disaffected by the corrupt bureaucracy of the Salliche government. The colonists chose Varonat because scouting reports showed unusually rich soil within the Great Jungle, but the soil's richness lasted only one season. The Morodins — immense sentient lizard-slug creatures — were initially treated as agricultural pests for spreading slime across the fields, though their slime actually enriches the soil in unusual ways. After Tropis' death, the colonists lost their resolve and depended on irregular supply shipments, with few having enough credits to leave. Located in the Ison Corridor of the Outer Rim.",
    locations: "Tropis-on-Varonat (The original colony settlement, now the planet's primary spaceport. About 30 dilapidated buildings nestled beneath pale yellow trees around a hacked-out landing field. Features a port facilities building, Great Jungle Outfitters shop run by Joodiel Amgris selling hunting gear to safari-goers, and a hotel that is reportedly nicer inside than it looks). Edgefields-on-Varonat (A second colony site established on the wide plains at the jungle's edge by settlers hoping to find better soil. Equally unsuccessful as Tropis-on-Varonat, it became the planet's other spaceport).",
    ofNote: "8 ABY: The Krish criminal Gamgalon established Morodin-hunting safaris that attracted off-planet traffic and slightly boosted the economy. The safaris were actually cover for a weapons-smuggling operation — aleudrupe berries grown in Morodin slime-saturated soil undergo a chemical change, and the pits become a catalyst that combines rethan-K and promhassic triaxli into blaster gas as powerful as spin-sealed Tibanna gas. The local Imperial governor was bribed to look the other way. Gamgalon's operation was disrupted by Talon Karrde and Mara Jade. | MORODINS: Fully sentient beings, 10-20 meters long, mottled yellow with spoonbill snouts, stubby legs, and wide teeth. They build elaborate mazes with their slime trails — a sign of intelligence the colonists never recognized. Population estimated at 50,000. Their slime enriches soil but also causes unusual chemical changes in certain plants. | JUNGLE: The Great Jungle of Varonat features pale yellow trees and yellow-green bushes with pale violet ground cover. Non-native yagaran aleudrupe plants grow where seeds have been dropped, producing berries considered a delicacy on many worlds. Transpond markers are hidden throughout the jungle from Gamgalon's planting and harvesting operations. | SAFARI: Gamgalon's safaris use three Aratech Arrow-17 airspeeders to fly hunters to a semi-permanent base camp (four buildings around a burned-off landing area, about one hour's flight from Tropis-on-Varonat). From there, hunting parties proceed on foot for 3-4 hours to reach Morodin territory. Safaris typically last upwards of four days and cost 12,000-17,000 credits per hunter."
