    source: "WEG40129 Adventure Journal 1 p.40",
    summary: "Druckenwell is a highly industrialized world with distinct classes of workers and corporate elite. Few of the 9.3 billion inhabitants live in the countryside — most are members of the worker class living and toiling in the planet's overcrowded cities. Cities were planned with the social and corporate order in mind, containing specific districts for corporate offices, worker class quarters and services, heavy industry, and park-like rural sections for corporate elite homes. The planet's several large cities and industrial regions are divided by vast oceans — whatever solid land was available was developed centuries ago.",
    locations: "II Avali (A major industrial city and home to I'att Armament's chief research and production facility. Features an Imperial-class spaceport, a dilapidated warehouse district surrounding the factory complex, and an entertainment quarter including Happy's Landing ale house known for spicy food and live music).",
    ofNote: "Druckenwell's corporate guilds have gone to great lengths to ensure industry does not pollute the few natural resources the planet has — cleansing air, soil and water is now one of the planet's major industries. Other major corporations serve the defense, computer and transportation industries. Strict population laws require couples to prove financial independence before legally marrying and bearing children. | I'ATT ARMAMENT: The I'att family corporation developed a prototype personal anti-energy field that made stormtrooper armor invulnerable to blaster fire. Moff Eisen Kerioth of the Doldur sector murdered the founders Strephan and Augusta I'att to seize the technology. The factory was destroyed when co-developer Daye Azur-Jamin backfed the facility's force shield into the power grid, killing Kerioth and his stormtroopers. Heiress Tinian I'att escaped with salvaged field components."
