    function: "Tourism",
    government: "Tourist Guild (leases planet from Empire)",
    techLevel: "Space",
    majorExports: "None",
    majorImports: "All (economy is not self-sufficient)",
    source: "WEG40129 Adventure Journal 1 p.59",
    summary: "Spira is a water world with a low axial tilt giving it a huge temperate zone. The tropical environment and lack of dangerous flora and fauna have made it one of the premier vacation spots within easy reach of the privileged Core Worlds elite. Thousands of islands speckle the surface, many bearing tourist resorts. Oceanfront bungalows once occupied by wealthy Old Republic citizens now house political officers and powerful Imperial servants. The official Imperial presence is minimal and low-key — a small garrison exists more for honor guards to vacationing Moffs than to impose the Emperor's will. A largely pro-Empire world.",
    locations: "Ataria Island (The best and most exclusive resort island on Spira. Beautiful beaches on the east side, spectacular sheer cliffs to the north and west, thousands of bungalows across gentle interior slopes, and a tourist city near the eastern beaches. Southern inlet has a large marina. Connected by an extensive monorail web. The spaceport — the only one receiving passenger liners — features red marble-plated landing pads with exotic planters and invisible force fields, plus a compound housing Imperial TIE fighters, blastboats, and shuttles). The Aspre Plunge (The most exclusive resort on Spira, built into the north cliff of Ataria Island. Dozens of stories high, dropping into the surf and 100 meters into an underwater ravine. Features a massive three-tiered casino with 30-meter transparisteel window overlooking coral reefs — upper level for card games in noise-dampened fields, middle tier for games of chance and a restaurant, lower level for physical games and an astonishingly well-stocked bar. Also contains dance rooms, hotel suites, spas, and dining rooms with panoramic underwater views).",
    ofNote: "WEAPONS BAN: Lethal weapons (damage above 2D) are banned. Stun guns permitted as personal defense. Sports weapons allowed. Travelers caught smuggling weapons receive a warning and confiscation. | TRAVEL RESTRICTIONS: Only passenger ships, contracted supply shuttles, and Imperial vessels may land and take off. No privately owned starships. | SPIRA REGATTA OPEN: Annual sailing race (345th as of this adventure), with the race route passing over popular diving sites including an ancient alien shipwreck in shallow water. The wreck is a popular tourist diving destination. | SECURITY: An independent Spira Security Police force manages day-to-day law enforcement, answering to the Spira government rather than the Empire. Officers wear tropical uniforms — off-white tunics, pressed khaki shorts, brown leather shoes, thick tan socks. They carry small blasters. Imperial stormtroopers remain in their compound except during emergencies. | CAMRAY EELS: Snakelike marine predators native to Spira, popular as hunting trophies among upper-class game hunters. Dead specimens have an incredibly potent smell requiring special sealed storage tanks — useful for discouraging customs inspections."
