    summary: "Najiba is a remote world, relatively isolated from its neighbors. An extended elliptical orbit offers a long growing season and shortened days. Due to the mysterious asteroid belt (called the Children of Najiba) which the planet passes near during one half of its orbital cycle, the planet is unreliable for continuous space traffic — when the asteroids are home, no traffic on or off the planet. A world of interminable extremes existing in perpetual spring, delineating seasons in terms of electrical disruptions and torrential rainstorms.",
    locations: "Reuther's Wetdock (A bar and landing pad run by the aging Najib bartender Reuther, a former bounty hunter. The open flight pad serves as a docking area for visiting smugglers and traders).",
    ofNote: "THE NAJIB: The native inhabitants are superstitious and wary of outsiders but offer the warmest hospitality. Easily adaptable and hardy workers, they are renowned for their loyalty. Despite their own lack of technology, they are knowledgeable and adept at using and repairing high-tech weaponry and spacecraft, partially due to a constant influx of smuggled goods. | THE CHILDREN OF NAJIBA: A mysterious asteroid belt that has claimed an orbit around the planet. When the asteroids are nearby during Najiba's elliptical orbit, all space traffic to and from the surface is forbidden — the rocks are too dangerous to navigate. This isolation makes Najiba a haven for smugglers willing to risk the asteroids."
